Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is an autoencoder?
AI Response

An autoencoder learns a compressed (latent) representation of input data through an encoder, then
reconstructs it with a decoder. Used for dimensionality reduction, denoising, and anomaly detection.

Example 1.2

User

What is a transformer model?
AI Response

A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.

Example 1.3

User

What is word embedding?
AI Response

Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.

Example 1.4

User

What is feature engineering?
AI Response

Feature engineering creates or transforms input variables using domain knowledge to improve model
performance. It includes scaling, encoding, and creating interaction terms.

Example 1.5

User

What is machine learning?
AI Response

Machine learning is a branch of artificial intelligence that enables systems to learn and improve from
experience without being explicitly programmed.

Example 1.6

User

What is precision vs recall?
AI Response

Precision is correct positive predictions / all positive predictions. Recall is correct positive predictions / all
actual positives. F1 score harmonically balances both.

Example 1.7

User

What is PCA?
AI Response



Principal Component Analysis reduces dimensionality by transforming data to axes of greatest variance. It
reduces noise, speeds up training, and helps visualize high-dimensional data.

Example 1.8

User

What is RLHF?
AI Response

Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback trains a reward model on human preference data, then uses
RL (PPO) to fine-tune an LLM to produce outputs humans prefer.

Example 1.9

User

What is mean squared error?
AI Response

MSE is (1/n) * sum of (predicted - actual)^2. It penalizes large errors heavily and is a standard loss function
for regression tasks, sensitive to outliers.

Example 1.10

User

What is the bias-variance tradeoff?
AI Response

High bias = underfitting (oversimplified model); high variance = overfitting (over-complex model). Good
models balance both to minimize total prediction error.



Section 2: Instruction Following

Example 2.1

User

Define 'empathy'.
AI Response

Empathy is the ability to understand and share the feelings of another person — to see a situation from their
perspective and feel what they feel.

